WEBVTT

00:12.346 --> 00:14.780
<i> WYATT: Hey, Mom.</i>

00:14.782 --> 00:16.648
<i> I'm doing all right.</i>

00:16.650 --> 00:20.052
<i> My narcolepsy is fine.</i>

00:20.054 --> 00:23.288
<i> No, I haven't been</i>
<i> sleeping on the floor.</i>

00:24.658 --> 00:28.060
<i> ¶¶ [guitar, whistling]</i>

00:28.062 --> 00:29.461
<i> I'm fine.</i>

00:31.766 --> 00:34.033
<i> Things have been good.</i>

00:34.035 --> 00:36.068
<i> Really...</i>

00:36.070 --> 00:37.436
<i> good.</i>

00:38.506 --> 00:39.605
<i> No.</i>

00:39.607 --> 00:41.640
<i> I have a job, remember?</i>

00:43.210 --> 00:45.444
<i> Okay, yeah,</i>
<i> I'm just a temp,</i>

00:45.446 --> 00:48.781
<i> but isn't every job</i>
<i> temporary?</i>

00:50.584 --> 00:52.284
<i> If you work anywhere</i>
<i> long enough,</i>

00:52.286 --> 00:54.820
<i> everyone's just a temp</i>
<i> in the end, right?</i>

00:54.822 --> 00:57.423
<i> We're temporary beings</i>
<i> is what I'm getting at.</i>

00:57.425 --> 00:59.291
<i> We all die eventually.</i>

01:00.661 --> 01:02.661
<i> Okay, I'm sorry.</i>

01:04.331 --> 01:06.498
<i> Didn't mean to be so dark.</i>

01:08.402 --> 01:12.271
<i> Yes, I'm still a temp.</i>

01:12.273 --> 01:14.273
<i> That's why I called.</i>

01:16.610 --> 01:19.411
[sighs] I'm gonna give them
an ultimatum today.

01:21.515 --> 01:24.316
So some support would be nice.

01:26.520 --> 01:27.719
Wait a second, Mom, hold on.

01:29.390 --> 01:31.590
What are you guys doing?

01:31.592 --> 01:35.627
Oh, hey, dude.
Just doing some day trading.

01:35.629 --> 01:37.196
And why are you doing it
up here in the living room

01:37.198 --> 01:39.832
and not downstairs
in your own bedroom?

01:39.834 --> 01:43.302
Well, we rented out our rooms
for the night.

01:43.304 --> 01:44.570
It's the sharing economy,
you know.

01:44.572 --> 01:46.105
Sharing is caring, Wyatt.

01:46.107 --> 01:48.240
Thank you, Barrett.

01:48.242 --> 01:50.375
What happened
to the flat screen?

01:50.377 --> 01:52.845
Yeah, we rented that out too.

01:52.847 --> 01:56.281
TV is gonna
rot your brain, Wyatt.

01:57.718 --> 02:00.552
Oh, okay.

02:00.554 --> 02:02.855
So who'd you rent
your rooms out to anyway?

02:02.857 --> 02:05.724
Oh, hey, look,
there's one of 'em right there.

02:05.726 --> 02:07.359
Hey, are you guys
gonna eat this?

02:07.361 --> 02:08.794
- Oh, hey, dude.
- Hi.

02:08.796 --> 02:11.497
- Hey, is that the gordita?
- Not the gordita.

02:11.499 --> 02:14.133
I'm sorry, Mom,
what were you saying again?

02:18.472 --> 02:19.638
Nothing.

02:19.640 --> 02:23.142
<i> ¶¶ [guitar continues]</i>

02:31.352 --> 02:33.485
Fine, Mom.

02:35.489 --> 02:37.489
I've been staying awake.

02:39.860 --> 02:42.194
So how's Dad?

02:42.196 --> 02:46.732
No, please,
don't put him on the phone.

02:46.734 --> 02:47.799
[sighs]

02:47.801 --> 02:49.535
Hi, Dad.

02:51.705 --> 02:56.241
I'm not quitting.
I'm just asking for a promotion.

02:58.345 --> 03:01.813
Yeah, I know, but I'm talking
about my career here, now.

03:03.584 --> 03:04.917
Whatever.

03:17.698 --> 03:19.531
Okay, I'll move home!

03:20.968 --> 03:22.968
If I don't get the job.

03:22.970 --> 03:24.836
But I'm gonna get it.

03:24.838 --> 03:26.405
Look, I gotta go.

03:26.407 --> 03:28.307
I'll talk to you
two later, okay?

03:32.313 --> 03:33.579
[engine starts]

03:57.304 --> 03:58.370
[car door closes]

04:12.386 --> 04:15.454
Okay, ending global hunger.

04:15.456 --> 04:17.456
Charities.

04:17.458 --> 04:19.324
Where's the new stuff
we were talking about?

04:19.326 --> 04:20.726
Well, on the top there,
there's an article

04:20.728 --> 04:21.860
about endangered tortoises.

04:21.862 --> 04:24.730
Endangered tortoises. Nice.

04:24.732 --> 04:26.498
Let me ask you a question.

04:26.500 --> 04:28.500
Who gives a, uh,

04:28.502 --> 04:32.037
flying fuck
about endangered tortoises?

04:32.039 --> 04:34.606
Okay, you know
what we publish here.

04:34.608 --> 04:38.010
Things like
homelessness, drugs,

04:38.012 --> 04:40.412
shameful deviant sex acts.

04:40.414 --> 04:44.016
Raw human emotion
with an emphasis on tragedy.

04:44.018 --> 04:45.951
But I can do that stuff too.

04:45.953 --> 04:49.588
Listen, bring me something
good for the website,

04:49.590 --> 04:52.591
and I'll consider it, okay?

04:52.593 --> 04:54.826
Until then, I've gotta
keep you where you're at.

04:54.828 --> 04:56.928
Thanks.

04:56.930 --> 05:01.600
Or, you know, you can consider
a different route,

05:01.602 --> 05:03.502
maybe a job in tech.

05:03.504 --> 05:05.504
I just--
You might not be cut out

05:05.506 --> 05:07.506
for being a journalist, bud.

05:17.318 --> 05:20.452
Are you--
Are you meditating?

05:22.423 --> 05:24.056
Wyatt!

05:24.058 --> 05:26.091
Wait, you okay?

05:26.093 --> 05:27.926
You need me to call you
an ambulance?

05:27.928 --> 05:30.729
No, no, I don't need
an ambulance. I just...

05:30.731 --> 05:33.632
I have narcolepsy.

05:33.634 --> 05:36.435
Mild narcolepsy.
It's not a big deal.

05:36.437 --> 05:38.437
You have fucking narcolepsy,
and you didn't think

05:38.439 --> 05:40.539
that would be something
pertinent to tell us?

05:40.541 --> 05:42.641
Fuckin' hell, man!

05:43.644 --> 05:45.377
Jesus Christ.

05:45.379 --> 05:46.745
Look, I'm sorry it happened.

05:46.747 --> 05:49.781
I'm sorry, I was just...
[mumbles]

05:49.783 --> 05:51.717
I just fuckin' fell asleep
in your office.

05:51.719 --> 05:53.418
You fall over,
you crack your fuckin' head,

05:53.420 --> 05:55.987
I've got a lawsuit
on my hands.

05:55.989 --> 05:58.623
I don't want a lawsuit
on my hands.

05:58.625 --> 05:59.791
The next time
you're in my office,

05:59.793 --> 06:02.794
you fucking wear a helmet!

06:15.542 --> 06:20.512
<i> ¶¶ [xylophone]</i>

06:22.116 --> 06:24.015
<i> ¶¶ [rock]</i>

06:24.017 --> 06:26.852
[cheering]

06:29.156 --> 06:31.423
Oh, excuse me, bud.

06:31.425 --> 06:34.459
<i> ¶¶ [continues]</i>

06:37.464 --> 06:39.598
[door closes]

06:39.600 --> 06:42.901
- Oh, you're back in your room.
- Oh, hey, man, what's up?

06:42.903 --> 06:44.770
No one told me that we're
having a party tonight.

06:44.772 --> 06:46.471
Yeah, it's just something
Barrett put together.

06:46.473 --> 06:48.740
Super low key.

06:48.742 --> 06:51.109
[man screaming]

06:51.111 --> 06:53.011
Sounds like it.

06:53.013 --> 06:54.646
So how'd it go today?

06:54.648 --> 06:57.048
I'm still a temp.

06:57.050 --> 06:59.918
That is so unjust, man.

06:59.920 --> 07:02.120
I think it's time for me
to pack up and go home.

07:02.122 --> 07:04.890
Stepping stones, man,
stepping stones.

07:04.892 --> 07:08.827
Dude, when I started my website,
it was just me and a dream.

07:08.829 --> 07:10.595
And now I've got
10 people underneath me.

07:10.597 --> 07:12.831
Right, and how much do you
pay these people again?

07:12.833 --> 07:15.200
$3 an hour.

07:15.202 --> 07:17.636
But that is
a really good rate in India.

07:17.638 --> 07:19.638
Microsoft,
those cheap bastards,

07:19.640 --> 07:21.473
are only paying
50 cents over there.

07:21.475 --> 07:23.675
$3, that's a lot, man.

07:23.677 --> 07:25.076
You're Mother Teresa,
Mahoney.

07:25.078 --> 07:26.778
Damn right I am.

07:26.780 --> 07:29.648
Hey, come upstairs
for a while.

07:29.650 --> 07:32.818
Maybe get drunk
and mush it in something.

07:32.820 --> 07:34.953
WYATT: Not very Teresa-like!

07:44.097 --> 07:47.599
<i> ANNOUNCER:</i>
<i> Welcome to the world of</i> Slice.

07:51.004 --> 07:53.939
I'm Sean Cross.
Tonight on<i> Slice News,</i>

07:53.941 --> 07:57.909
Wayne Bradshaw takes you
to the worst shooting gallery

07:57.911 --> 08:00.078
in the entire
Western hemisphere.

08:00.080 --> 08:02.247
Let's go to Wayne now.

08:02.249 --> 08:03.748
Wayne, are you there?

08:03.750 --> 08:05.517
We've got junkies galore
out here, Sean.

08:05.519 --> 08:07.519
They call this neighborhood
The Haystack

08:07.521 --> 08:08.787
'cause there's needles
everywhere.

08:08.789 --> 08:10.822
Watch your step.
Here we go.

08:10.824 --> 08:14.025
We got a couple people ready
to shoot up right now.

08:14.027 --> 08:16.795
Let's get a close-up
on that needle.

08:16.797 --> 08:20.799
Ooh, that's some great needle
footage, Wayne. Super gross.

08:20.801 --> 08:24.102
WAYNE: You guys are out here
doing drugs every day, huh?

08:24.104 --> 08:26.838
Yeah, you want some?

08:26.840 --> 08:28.940
These guys are basically
fucked, Sean.

08:28.942 --> 08:30.208
There's no hope for 'em.

08:30.210 --> 08:31.910
They really, really are.

08:31.912 --> 08:33.712
Looks super sketchy
down there, Wayne.

08:33.714 --> 08:35.680
Smells like human feces
out here, Sean.

08:35.682 --> 08:37.916
People don't just come fuckin'
take a shit at your house.

08:37.918 --> 08:40.685
SEAN: Why don't you get
some more injection close-ups?

08:40.687 --> 08:43.021
Show me some blood.

08:43.023 --> 08:45.590
Could you guys shoot up
just like one more time?

08:45.592 --> 08:47.158
We didn't really get
a clean take on that.

08:47.160 --> 08:48.960
JUNKIE: You can just
shoot up your--

08:50.531 --> 08:52.731
<i> ¶¶ [rock]</i>

08:52.733 --> 08:55.200
[yelling]

09:00.574 --> 09:01.973
Damn, Gina.

09:01.975 --> 09:03.875
Oh, hey, Barrett.

09:03.877 --> 09:05.610
Hey, listen, I want you
to meet my friends.

09:05.612 --> 09:07.679
- Hi.
- This is Claire.

09:07.681 --> 09:09.214
This is Stephanie.
They're from New Zealand.

09:09.216 --> 09:10.649
They're staying with us
for the week.

09:10.651 --> 09:13.885
- Hey, how you doing?
- Baby bird!

09:13.887 --> 09:15.820
That was so sick!

09:15.822 --> 09:18.623
Oh, you're pretty good.
That's gonna be good!

09:18.625 --> 09:20.158
Bawk bawk!

09:20.160 --> 09:22.227
[soft chatter]

09:28.335 --> 09:30.201
- Nothing like modified.
- No difference.

09:30.203 --> 09:31.870
- Hey.
- Hey.

09:31.872 --> 09:34.606
Look who decided
to come out of his cave.

09:34.608 --> 09:37.642
You know, I can't tell
who lives here at this point.

09:37.644 --> 09:40.111
Feel like I'm living
in a flophouse.

09:40.113 --> 09:43.582
Hey, you read the search terms
on the Craigslist ad.

09:43.584 --> 09:48.753
Kegs, 420 friendly,
bacchanalia, debauchery.

09:48.755 --> 09:51.356
Hey, have you ever noticed
that hatchback over there?

09:52.960 --> 09:56.661
Yeah, I think it's been
there for a few months.

09:56.663 --> 09:59.898
Some weird girl
lives inside of it.

09:59.900 --> 10:01.733
That's what you get when
you have good street parking.

10:01.735 --> 10:03.735
It's like a beacon
for transients.

10:03.737 --> 10:05.870
I wonder who she is.

10:05.872 --> 10:07.973
Listen, man, I think
we need to collectively

10:07.975 --> 10:10.275
raise our standards
as a household.

10:11.878 --> 10:14.346
We do not need another
drifter in this house.

10:21.888 --> 10:23.788
<i> SEAN: You know</i>
<i> what we publish here.</i>

10:23.790 --> 10:26.157
<i> Homelessness, drugs,</i>

10:26.159 --> 10:30.028
<i> raw human emotion</i>
<i> with an emphasis on tragedy.</i>

10:30.030 --> 10:34.265
<i> ¶¶</i>

11:06.233 --> 11:09.434
- Okay, I'll leave.
- You don't have to leave.

11:09.436 --> 11:11.403
It's a great spot.

11:11.405 --> 11:13.405
That's why you knocked
on my window?

11:13.407 --> 11:15.974
To compliment
my choice in parking?

11:15.976 --> 11:17.442
No.

11:19.112 --> 11:20.311
You know me, right?

11:20.313 --> 11:22.414
You-- I mean, you see me.

11:22.416 --> 11:24.849
I live right around
the corner.

11:24.851 --> 11:26.751
We're like neighbors.

11:26.753 --> 11:31.256
I guess I was just
being neighborly.

11:31.258 --> 11:33.224
Okay.

11:33.226 --> 11:35.827
Hi, neighbor.

11:35.829 --> 11:37.128
I'm Wyatt.

11:38.265 --> 11:40.899
Fern.

11:40.901 --> 11:43.468
So what do you
really want, Wyatt?

11:45.839 --> 11:47.906
I guess I just wanna
get to know you.

11:47.908 --> 11:51.242
What's a girl, who doesn't
seem like a drug addict,

11:51.244 --> 11:53.344
doing all the way
from Montana,

11:53.346 --> 11:56.014
living in her
'88 hatchback?

11:56.016 --> 11:59.451
Well, it's an '87,
and I'm a total meth head,

11:59.453 --> 12:00.485
You got any?

12:00.487 --> 12:02.120
Um...

12:02.122 --> 12:04.289
Was I really that convincing?

12:04.291 --> 12:07.759
No, no, of course not.
Um...

12:07.761 --> 12:10.128
You want a car-warming present?

12:10.130 --> 12:12.964
Oh, because at the very least,
I must be an alcoholic, right?

12:12.966 --> 12:15.400
No, obviously not.

12:15.402 --> 12:16.968
Girl living in her car,

12:16.970 --> 12:19.137
there's gotta be
something wrong with her.

12:19.139 --> 12:20.271
This was stupid.

12:20.273 --> 12:22.107
I'm really sorry
and embarrassed,

12:22.109 --> 12:23.742
so I'm gonna leave you.

12:23.744 --> 12:26.911
You have a good night.

12:26.913 --> 12:28.146
Wait, don't go.

12:28.148 --> 12:30.215
I mean, I don't
wanna get arrested

12:30.217 --> 12:33.351
for soliciting
a prostitute, so...

12:33.353 --> 12:35.153
just get in.

12:35.155 --> 12:38.056
You want me
to get inside there?

12:38.058 --> 12:40.158
Yeah.

12:40.160 --> 12:42.160
Come on, give me that.

12:56.409 --> 12:58.543
This isn't so bad, actually.

13:03.150 --> 13:04.315
Why here?

13:07.154 --> 13:09.487
A lot of people
park on this block.

13:11.792 --> 13:14.325
See that red truck back there?

13:14.327 --> 13:17.996
This construction worker
parks there every day.

13:17.998 --> 13:19.531
He leaves on the weekends,

13:19.533 --> 13:22.500
probably to go back
to see his wife and kids.

13:22.502 --> 13:24.836
And that little white car
right there,

13:24.838 --> 13:27.205
this old woman named Margaret
lives there.

13:27.207 --> 13:29.107
She's from Vermont.

13:29.109 --> 13:32.477
So basically like
any car with shades on?

13:32.479 --> 13:34.379
Yeah, or else it'll steam up
from your breath,

13:34.381 --> 13:36.214
and cops look for steam.

13:37.284 --> 13:38.917
Where do you shower?

13:38.919 --> 13:41.452
Who says that I do?

13:41.454 --> 13:43.454
You smell like
Head & Shoulders.

13:44.925 --> 13:46.825
The YWCA.

13:46.827 --> 13:52.130
Do you like always let
strangers into your car?

13:52.132 --> 13:55.466
No, but when I read
your articles,

13:55.468 --> 13:58.970
I knew you were harmless.

13:58.972 --> 14:01.472
You stole my stuff?

14:01.474 --> 14:04.108
You threw it in the trash.

14:04.110 --> 14:07.045
I mean, what kind of guy
who writes about pet adoptions

14:07.047 --> 14:09.881
and county fairs
would hurt me?

14:09.883 --> 14:11.382
Besides, I need something to do

14:11.384 --> 14:13.451
while I'm sitting here
all night.

14:15.488 --> 14:17.856
Well, I guess it could make
good toilet paper.

14:18.859 --> 14:21.960
I don't have a toilet.

14:21.962 --> 14:26.097
There's some pretty good
stuff in here, like...

14:27.601 --> 14:29.334
Something about tortoises.

14:29.336 --> 14:31.502
Yeah, I know.
I wrote about tortoises.

14:31.504 --> 14:34.472
No, seriously. I mean...

14:34.474 --> 14:36.374
they've been adapting
to the deserts for eons,

14:36.376 --> 14:38.509
and then we just come through
with our strip malls

14:38.511 --> 14:42.547
and gas stations and just
pave right over their homes.

14:42.549 --> 14:44.449
It's so sad.

14:44.451 --> 14:46.951
Yeah, it is.

14:46.953 --> 14:48.953
That's why I wrote it.

14:51.458 --> 14:53.925
It's too bad nobody
gives a shit, I guess.

14:53.927 --> 14:57.195
I give a shit.
I give lots of shits.

14:57.197 --> 14:58.263
I mean...

14:58.265 --> 15:00.298
I know what you mean.

15:02.469 --> 15:05.336
Why are you here?

15:05.338 --> 15:09.574
I work for this company
called Slice.

15:09.576 --> 15:13.678
It's not working out
so well though, so...

15:13.680 --> 15:16.614
I think I'm just
probably gonna go home.

15:16.616 --> 15:19.117
That shitty clickbait company?

15:19.119 --> 15:20.251
Yep.

15:20.253 --> 15:21.586
Your stuff's better than that.

15:21.588 --> 15:23.454
Gee, thanks.

15:26.993 --> 15:28.559
Who's he?

15:28.561 --> 15:30.295
No one.

15:31.698 --> 15:35.500
I mean, he's like
everywhere on your car.

15:35.502 --> 15:38.303
Can you take the hint that
I don't wanna talk about it?

15:38.305 --> 15:41.205
Sorry. I was just
trying to be friendly.

15:51.451 --> 15:54.085
He's my dad, all right?

15:59.326 --> 16:01.559
Did they ever find him?

16:01.561 --> 16:04.295
No. Assumed dead
since I was nine.

16:04.297 --> 16:07.165
Then I got this
a few months ago.

16:14.174 --> 16:17.442
"Dear Fern,
your father needs your help.

16:17.444 --> 16:19.210
He's in Los Angeles.

16:19.212 --> 16:21.446
Sincerely, Dr. Green."

16:21.448 --> 16:22.747
Dr. Green?

16:22.749 --> 16:24.983
Some street guy.

16:24.985 --> 16:27.251
We searched the shelters
and databases,

16:27.253 --> 16:29.420
but can't find him.

16:29.422 --> 16:30.588
If you need to,
you can stay on our couch.

16:30.590 --> 16:32.023
We have surfers all the time.

16:32.025 --> 16:34.359
I don't surf on couches.

16:34.361 --> 16:38.262
- We have a shower and a toilet.
- I'm fine on my own.

16:38.264 --> 16:41.632
I don't what to say.
I just wanna...

16:41.634 --> 16:43.368
do something.

16:45.071 --> 16:46.637
Thanks, Wyatt.

16:51.411 --> 16:53.544
Hey, wake up.

17:00.320 --> 17:02.020
Oh, my God.

17:03.590 --> 17:06.524
Sorry. I guess
I overstayed my welcome.

17:06.526 --> 17:09.560
I deserve it for getting
drunk with a stranger.

17:09.562 --> 17:11.496
What about you?

17:11.498 --> 17:14.298
You just slept
in a weird girl's car.

17:14.300 --> 17:17.335
You should really think
about that, Wyatt.

17:19.672 --> 17:21.039
Okay.

17:24.477 --> 17:26.711
I'm kinda kidding.

17:28.181 --> 17:29.614
But kinda not.

17:29.616 --> 17:31.783
You wanna come inside?
I'll make you breakfast.

17:31.785 --> 17:34.452
I don't belong in your world.

17:40.193 --> 17:42.193
Well, maybe you should
give me your number

17:42.195 --> 17:44.128
- in case you need anything.
- I don't have a phone.

17:44.130 --> 17:45.596
Well, then maybe
I can find you one.

17:45.598 --> 17:47.832
I don't want it.
The Internet's terrifying.

17:47.834 --> 17:51.769
I've got laundry to do
and then I have work, so...

17:51.771 --> 17:53.371
- Work?
- Yeah.

17:53.373 --> 17:54.772
I work at the thrift store.

17:54.774 --> 17:56.841
Where do you think
I get all these cool rags?

17:58.278 --> 18:00.178
Well, it was nice talking.

