your dad has great taste

28:07.219 --> 28:09.987
in getaway locations.

28:09.989 --> 28:11.989
He must love it here.

28:11.991 --> 28:17.127
Was he, um, decent
when he was around?

28:17.129 --> 28:20.064
Yeah, from what I remember.

28:20.066 --> 28:23.367
I mean, sometimes
I'd look into his eyes,

28:23.369 --> 28:25.736
and he just wasn't there.

28:27.206 --> 28:29.106
My grandparents said
the last time they saw him,

28:29.108 --> 28:33.777
he was slow dancing with a
Barbie doll in the living room.

28:35.014 --> 28:36.480
Well, maybe
they ran away together

28:36.482 --> 28:39.016
and started a family.

28:39.018 --> 28:40.884
That'd be nice.

28:49.228 --> 28:50.994
WYATT: Are you scared?

28:52.465 --> 28:54.998
I'm always scared.

29:06.145 --> 29:08.278
Anybody home?

29:10.483 --> 29:12.750
Hey, look at this.

29:15.254 --> 29:17.187
Hello?

29:17.189 --> 29:19.089
Think I could fit in here?

29:19.091 --> 29:20.424
No, don't do that, Fern.

29:20.426 --> 29:22.926
- I think so.
- Fern, seriously?

29:22.928 --> 29:24.328
- Yeah.
- Fern!

29:29.435 --> 29:31.201
Whoa.

29:31.203 --> 29:33.871
It's so cool in here.

29:33.873 --> 29:35.973
Hey, you should come in here.

29:35.975 --> 29:38.842
Nah, I'm not really
a derelict-structure kinda guy.

29:43.082 --> 29:44.915
He's here!

29:44.917 --> 29:47.151
He's-- He's in there?

29:48.954 --> 29:50.487
- Garbage?
- No.

29:50.489 --> 29:53.190
Sardines.
They were his favorite.

29:55.094 --> 29:56.994
Those could be anybody's.
You know that, right?

29:56.996 --> 29:59.429
No, it's his brand:
Beach Cliff.

29:59.431 --> 30:01.265
He's here.
He's definitely here.

30:01.267 --> 30:02.833
Come on,
we have to go find him.

30:02.835 --> 30:04.201
- Okay.
- Come on!

30:04.203 --> 30:07.070
