and I am fine ¶

35:30.896 --> 35:32.429
Nice to meet you, sir.

35:32.431 --> 35:33.563
Hey.

35:33.565 --> 35:36.433
Don't say "sir."
Say "bro."

35:36.435 --> 35:37.634
You haven't met Farid yet.

35:37.636 --> 35:39.136
No, I have not.

35:39.138 --> 35:40.804
Yeah, he just got in
from Delhi.

35:40.806 --> 35:42.739
He's one of my employees
over there.

35:42.741 --> 35:46.476
Nice to meet you, bro.

35:48.280 --> 35:50.547
Ooh, you gotta let
those cool down, dude.

35:50.549 --> 35:51.882
They are very hot.

35:51.884 --> 35:54.317
So anyway, uh...

35:54.319 --> 35:57.554
kinda have Fern coming over.

35:57.556 --> 35:59.356
Cool.
The homeless chick, right?

35:59.358 --> 36:01.825
Let's not call her that
ever again,

36:01.827 --> 36:03.560
if you don't mind.

36:03.562 --> 36:04.895
And if it's at all possible
for you guys

36:04.897 --> 36:08.632
maybe to like,
I don't know, clear out?

36:08.634 --> 36:09.833
[knocking]

36:09.835 --> 36:11.902
Or not.

36:11.904 --> 36:14.704
[sighs]
Come in!

36:16.775 --> 36:18.175
[door closes]

36:20.579 --> 36:22.646
Guys, this is Fern.

36:24.550 --> 36:25.582
Hi.

36:29.955 --> 36:32.589
Hi. These are my roommates.

36:32.591 --> 36:34.691
I'm Barrett.
How do you do?

36:34.693 --> 36:36.593
It's nice to finally meet you.

36:36.595 --> 36:38.361
Hello.

36:38.363 --> 36:39.829
We've heard so much about you.

36:39.831 --> 36:42.699
So you know
why I'm here then.

36:42.701 --> 36:44.734
I think you're going
to dinner, right?

36:47.472 --> 36:51.575
To save your souls
from the coming apocalypse.

36:52.978 --> 36:54.844
What?

36:54.846 --> 36:57.948
The government's
watching us right now.

36:57.950 --> 37:00.617
CIA, NSA, FBI,

37:00.619 --> 37:03.286
Homeland Security.

37:03.288 --> 37:04.854
Everybody knows that.
It was on<i> 60 Minutes.</i>

37:04.856 --> 37:06.489
No, seriously.

37:07.960 --> 37:09.993
They've got
this whole place bugged.

37:14.566 --> 37:17.434
They're all working together
to orchestrate this one.

37:17.436 --> 37:19.669
The end of humanity.

37:19.671 --> 37:21.671
We must go underground!

37:21.673 --> 37:23.907
They're listening to us
right now, I promise.

37:23.909 --> 37:25.875
We have to fight back.

37:25.877 --> 37:26.977
Really, bro?

37:26.979 --> 37:28.278
Really, bro!

37:28.280 --> 37:30.247
We have to fight
the bastards.

37:32.451 --> 37:33.883
You have to help yourself.

37:33.885 --> 37:35.852
You know the truth.
I can see it in your eyes!

37:35.854 --> 37:38.421
- I don't.
- Fern, let's just get going.

37:38.423 --> 37:39.856
We have a reservation.

37:39.858 --> 37:42.692
Just calm down.
Just look at me.

37:42.694 --> 37:44.995
Look at me, Fern. Listen to me.
Fern, can you hear me?

37:44.997 --> 37:47.564
Fern, Fern, look at me, please.
Look at me, Fern!

37:47.566 --> 37:49.799
Can you hear me?
Fern, are you there?

37:52.471 --> 37:54.638
Oh, my God, that's--

37:54.640 --> 37:57.440
- [laughing]
- You are--

37:57.442 --> 37:59.776
You're certifiably insane.

37:59.778 --> 38:02.912
Come on, let's go to dinner.

38:04.583 --> 38:06.883
I gotta say,

38:06.885 --> 38:09.286
your level of commitment
is really commendable.

38:09.288 --> 38:12.889
Guess I'm just not great
with first impressions.

38:12.891 --> 38:15.525
You know, they're never
gonna let you come back.

38:15.527 --> 38:17.494
That was my intention.

38:17.496 --> 38:19.663
[laughing]

38:24.403 --> 38:26.569
I'm sorry I couldn't take you
to a real restaurant.

38:26.571 --> 38:28.505
Don't worry about it.
I live off of this stuff.

38:28.507 --> 38:31.007
I know what time
every fast-food breakfast ends.

38:31.009 --> 38:32.575
That's an admirable quality.

38:32.577 --> 38:35.078
Seriously, try me.

38:35.080 --> 38:36.846
Um, Burger King.

38:36.848 --> 38:37.981
12:00.

38:37.983 --> 38:40.317
- Taco Bell.
- 11:00.

38:40.319 --> 38:41.484
- Arby's.
- Yuck.

38:41.486 --> 38:43.420
I'd rather skip breakfast.

38:43.422 --> 38:45.755
I thought vegetarians
were like huge foodies.

38:45.757 --> 38:48.758
I can't afford to be a foodie.
[chuckles]

38:48.760 --> 38:50.727
Of course.

38:50.729 --> 38:54.064
- I live in my car...
- Mm-hmm.

38:54.066 --> 38:56.066
I eat french fries.

38:56.068 --> 38:59.102
I guess you do make a point.

39:03.975 --> 39:07.510
And seriously though,
that girl's mental.

39:07.512 --> 39:10.080
Honestly, it probably was
the best date I've ever gone on.

39:10.082 --> 39:12.582
Date?

39:12.584 --> 39:14.484
Chill with a girl.

39:14.486 --> 39:17.387
Either way, it was amazing.

39:17.389 --> 39:20.824
Whoa, dude.
Where'd you learn that?

39:20.826 --> 39:22.359
Saw it online.

39:22.361 --> 39:23.827
- So guess what.
- What?

39:23.829 --> 39:25.495
I finished the article,

39:25.497 --> 39:27.097
and<i> Slice</i> is gonna
put it on the website.

39:27.099 --> 39:29.466
No shit!
Hey, congrats, dude.

39:29.468 --> 39:31.634
Yeah, it's a good thing
we got going.

39:31.636 --> 39:35.438
For you and her,
or you and the job?

39:35.440 --> 39:37.774
Both?

39:40.979 --> 39:43.513
Hey, I think our form
is looking pretty good.

39:43.515 --> 39:44.647
Yeah?

39:44.649 --> 39:46.149
I think we're ready.

39:46.151 --> 39:48.451
- Okay, let's go.
- Let's do it.

39:48.453 --> 39:52.655
So what happens
after she finds daddio?

39:54.559 --> 39:56.926
I don't know.
I'll just play it by ear.

39:57.929 --> 39:58.962
- Shit!
- No.

39:58.964 --> 40:00.130
Whew!

40:03.502 --> 40:05.502
MAHONEY:
I think we need wetsuits.

40:06.838 --> 40:08.438
- Nother day.
- Nother day.

40:12.644 --> 40:15.745
<i> ¶¶ [guitar]</i>

40:20.752 --> 40:23.586
<i> SEAN: Oh, Wyatt, my man,</i>
<i> there you are.</i>

40:23.588 --> 40:25.488
<i> Listen, great work</i>
<i> on the article.</i>

40:25.490 --> 40:27.690
Yeah, thanks,
I appreciate it.

40:27.692 --> 40:30.427
I'm just curious why
you changed the title though.

40:30.429 --> 40:31.995
I never said I slept with her.

40:31.997 --> 40:34.130
<i> Buddy, it's clickbait.</i>
<i> And you know what?</i>

40:34.132 --> 40:37.033
<i> It's fuckin' working 'cause</i>
<i> people are clicking, okay?</i>

40:37.035 --> 40:39.736
<i> You're not gonna believe it.</i>
<i> It's the top link on the site.</i>

40:39.738 --> 40:41.171
<i> People are sharing it.</i>

40:41.173 --> 40:43.006
<i> They wanna know</i>
<i> what's gonna happen.</i>

40:43.008 --> 40:45.542
<i> Listen, I can't wait</i>
<i> for the next installment.</i>

40:45.544 --> 40:47.210
<i> The readers can't wait</i>
<i> for the next installment.</i>

40:47.212 --> 40:50.980
<i> Take the rest of the month off</i>
<i> and finish the story.</i>

40:54.719 --> 40:56.486
[pats table]

41:02.527 --> 41:04.928
WYATT: I think they're closed.

41:04.930 --> 41:06.930
We have to get in.

41:11.102 --> 41:13.069
It's open.

41:13.071 --> 41:14.971
Damn it.

41:19.778 --> 41:21.978
FERN: Hello.

41:29.621 --> 41:32.856
FERN: This must have been
a really classy hotel.

41:34.526 --> 41:37.627
Do you really think
your dad would live in here?

41:37.629 --> 41:39.496
I don't know.

41:39.498 --> 41:41.764
Probably.

41:41.766 --> 41:43.166
What's over here?

41:47.205 --> 41:48.605
Hello.

41:51.543 --> 41:54.210
Anybody up here?

41:54.212 --> 41:56.813
If you are, don't jump out
and surprise us.

41:56.815 --> 42:00.283
Just... say hello.

42:01.786 --> 42:03.653
You know, the more we hang out,

42:03.655 --> 42:06.089
the more my life is starting
to look like a horror film.

42:07.726 --> 42:09.158
You're welcome.

42:15.867 --> 42:17.867
Wanna take a bubble bath?

42:20.539 --> 42:22.839
Go for it.

42:24.075 --> 42:25.775
Hey, look.

42:29.147 --> 42:31.014
Look at this.

42:39.791 --> 42:42.559
It's him, all right.

42:42.561 --> 42:44.894
"Lynn Blade Asylum?"

42:44.896 --> 42:49.299
"Diagnosis: bipolar disorder
with schizoid tendencies

42:49.301 --> 42:52.001
and suicidal ideation?"

42:52.003 --> 42:54.337
Jesus, Dad,
what don't you have?

42:54.339 --> 42:56.139
You look surprised.

42:56.141 --> 43:00.877
It's weird seeing it written out
officially like this.

43:00.879 --> 43:03.680
They used electric shock.

43:04.683 --> 43:07.183
Geez, they still do that?

43:09.654 --> 43:10.653
[door slams]

43:11.990 --> 43:14.290
- Let's run.
- Let's get out of here.

43:17.796 --> 43:20.296
- Which way is out?
- I don't know. This way.

43:20.298 --> 43:21.598
Aah!

43:21.600 --> 43:23.666
Oh, my God, are you okay?

43:27.172 --> 43:28.972
Ow. Looks like it hurts.

43:28.974 --> 43:30.173
Ah!

43:31.176 --> 43:32.375
When you do that.

43:32.377 --> 43:34.243
Sorry.

43:34.245 --> 43:37.280
Ow. Okay.
I'm gonna wrap it up.

43:37.282 --> 43:41.250
It's like very bruised.

43:41.252 --> 43:42.852
Oops.

43:46.691 --> 43:48.992
- Is that okay?
- Yeah.

43:52.097 --> 43:54.397
Good as new.

43:56.201 --> 43:57.700
Thanks.

43:57.702 --> 43:58.768
Yeah.

44:04.643 --> 44:06.776
<i> ¶¶</i>

44:14.052 --> 44:17.220
So what are the illustrations
all about?

44:17.222 --> 44:20.723
I don't know, just...

44:20.725 --> 44:23.960
things I imagine while
I'm lying here at night.

44:25.296 --> 44:27.030
Can I have this one?

44:27.032 --> 44:29.332
You like Dick-Nose Fern?

44:29.334 --> 44:32.735
Yeah, I think she's beautiful.

44:32.737 --> 44:35.071
She's all yours.

44:35.073 --> 44:36.239
Here.

44:38.710 --> 44:40.376
- Thanks.
- Yeah.

44:57.395 --> 44:58.728
Hey, guys.

45:01.032 --> 45:02.398
What's up?

45:02.400 --> 45:04.267
Have a seat, buddy.

45:05.403 --> 45:06.836
Okay.

45:06.838 --> 45:09.972
What is this,
like some sort of...

45:09.974 --> 45:11.908
family meeting?

45:13.278 --> 45:15.712
No.

45:15.714 --> 45:18.214
- Listen, I just--
- It's an intervention, Wyatt.

45:18.216 --> 45:20.349
Intervention.

45:20.351 --> 45:22.251
I'm gonna begin by reading
my letter, but before I do,

45:22.253 --> 45:25.054
I want you to know...

45:25.056 --> 45:28.291
everyone in this room
loves you very much.

45:28.293 --> 45:32.729
"Dear Wyatt, you've been
a really great friend of mine

45:32.731 --> 45:35.898
for a long time.

45:35.900 --> 45:37.300
I miss you, buddy."

45:37.302 --> 45:39.168
MAHONEY: Shut up, Barrett.

45:39.170 --> 45:41.003
Ever since...

45:41.005 --> 45:43.940
you met that homeless chick,

45:43.942 --> 45:45.975
you've put us
on the back burner.

45:45.977 --> 45:49.011
Now all you do is you
trample around the city

45:49.013 --> 45:51.147
on all these little
adventures.

45:51.149 --> 45:53.750
And what about us, man?

45:56.421 --> 45:59.489
You've gotta get help, Wyatt!

45:59.491 --> 46:01.090
Beautiful.

46:02.761 --> 46:04.827
Does anyone wanna
maybe tell me

46:04.829 --> 46:07.130
what the fuck
is going on right now?

46:08.500 --> 46:10.500
I've done some research
on Fern.

46:10.502 --> 46:12.835
What? Why?

46:12.837 --> 46:15.505
She's not who she says she is.
She's making it all up.

46:15.507 --> 46:17.507
She's a faker, bro.

46:17.509 --> 46:19.275
Farid, what, you too?

46:20.512 --> 46:22.078
That's right, Farid.

46:22.080 --> 46:23.913
She's a charlatan, dude.

46:23.915 --> 46:25.248
That's not--

46:25.250 --> 46:27.083
Yeah, she's like a gypsy.

46:27.085 --> 46:30.153
She's after something.
I mean, it's clear.

46:30.155 --> 46:31.554
No, fuck it--

46:31.556 --> 46:33.189
That guy that you've
been trying to find,

46:33.191 --> 46:34.323
it can't be her dad, okay?

46:34.325 --> 46:36.459
She's from Arizona.

46:36.461 --> 46:38.795
And, dude...

46:38.797 --> 46:40.396
she's married.

46:40.398 --> 46:44.033
- Please! That's bullshit.
- It's all online.

46:44.035 --> 46:45.835
She doesn't even have
a fucking Internet connection,

46:45.837 --> 46:47.336
let alone a cell phone.

46:53.845 --> 46:56.245
MAHONEY: Fern Montgomery.

46:56.247 --> 46:58.247
From Scottsdale.

46:59.818 --> 47:03.319
She's running away
from her old life, man.

47:03.321 --> 47:05.054
Don't kill the messenger, bro.

47:05.056 --> 47:06.889
Fuckin' A, Farid.

47:06.891 --> 47:09.926
Sorry. I'm just trying to help.
Hey, where are you going?

47:14.065 --> 47:16.465
Oh, excuse me.

47:16.467 --> 47:19.368
Would you take a dollar
for this toaster oven?

47:19.370 --> 47:21.270
Oh, it's $3.

47:21.272 --> 47:24.106
It has a great big dent in it.
See right there?

47:24.108 --> 47:26.542
Yeah, that's why it's $3.

47:26.544 --> 47:29.278
How about $2?

47:29.280 --> 47:32.048
I'm sorry.
It's already only $3.

47:32.050 --> 47:34.917
How come you won't work with me?
I come in here all the time.

47:34.919 --> 47:37.453
All the proceeds
go to charity, so...

47:37.455 --> 47:41.157
Why does this store
suck so bad?

47:41.159 --> 47:44.427
Right, well, um, it's $3.

47:44.429 --> 47:47.296
Let me know if you would
like to buy it. Thanks.

47:47.298 --> 47:49.365
[bells jingle]

47:52.136 --> 47:54.570
So you heard about
the toaster sale too?

47:54.572 --> 47:56.973
Sure, Mrs. Montgomery.

47:59.210 --> 48:02.111
That's not my name anymore.

48:04.115 --> 48:06.983
Hey, you shouldn't bring
your domestic disputes

48:06.985 --> 48:08.384
into the workplace.

48:08.386 --> 48:10.019
Very unprofessional!

48:10.021 --> 48:12.889
Just take the dang toaster,
lady, okay?

48:12.891 --> 48:15.892
No! I don't want it anymore!

48:18.630 --> 48:22.365
I'm never coming back
to this stupid store again!

48:22.367 --> 48:25.101
Look, I don't owe you anything,
all right?

48:25.103 --> 48:26.903
You decided to help me,
remember?

48:26.905 --> 48:29.605
Oh, no, I remember
I totally fell for the bait.

48:29.607 --> 48:32.208
I just wanna know
what the hell's going on.

48:32.210 --> 48:34.377
What is this all about
anyway?

48:34.379 --> 48:36.312
I mean, is...

48:36.314 --> 48:38.247
Is Simon even your real dad?

48:39.450 --> 48:42.518
Just leave me alone, Wyatt.

48:42.520 --> 48:44.687
Hey, where are you going?

48:44.689 --> 48:46.322
Hey, you can't leave!

48:46.324 --> 48:48.958
What about the store?

48:48.960 --> 48:52.094
Um, honor system,
everyone, okay?

48:52.096 --> 48:54.597
Just name your price and
leave the money on the counter.

48:54.599 --> 49:00.102
<i> ¶¶</i>

49:00.104 --> 49:04.674
<i> ¶¶ [continues]</i>

50:15.013 --> 50:16.579
I just...

50:20.551 --> 50:23.252
I just want you to be
who I think you are.

50:25.523 --> 50:27.723
I like that person.

50:30.028 --> 50:32.094
I want her to be real.

50:32.096 --> 50:33.596
I'm sorry about the way
I acted earlier.

50:33.598 --> 50:36.232
- I was being a jerk.
- It doesn't matter.

50:36.234 --> 50:38.234
I didn't want you to think
I was a bigger mess

50:38.236 --> 50:40.302
than I already am.

50:40.304 --> 50:44.607
My mom died three years
after Simon disappeared.

50:44.609 --> 50:47.243
My godparents in Arizona
adopted me.

50:55.153 --> 50:56.752
I'm sorry.

50:56.754 --> 50:59.522
It's not your fault.

50:59.524 --> 51:01.223
She liked pills.

51:03.294 --> 51:06.262
The hatchback was hers.

51:06.264 --> 51:10.266
I used to sleep in it at night
in my godparents' driveway.

51:12.136 --> 51:14.437
It still had her scent
back then.

51:17.742 --> 51:20.209
Are you married?

51:20.211 --> 51:23.412
Legally, yeah,

51:23.414 --> 51:26.849
but not emotionally.

51:26.851 --> 51:28.617
I never really loved him much.

51:28.619 --> 51:31.554
Do you think he's out there
looking for you?

51:31.556 --> 51:36.425
No. When I got Green's letter,
I saw it as my chance to leave.

51:39.130 --> 51:41.664
Tomorrow we'll go talk
to Dr. Green.

51:43.501 --> 51:45.367
What's the use?

51:45.369 --> 51:50.106
Well, this is beyond you now.
I'm invested in this.

51:50.108 --> 51:52.641
Well, that really
sucks for you, Wyatt.

51:52.643 --> 51:54.543
Seriously, it does.

51:54.545 --> 51:56.579
Well, I guess I don't care.

52:01.586 --> 52:04.553
WYATT: Maybe we'll see
the green flash tonight.

52:04.555 --> 52:05.855
What's that?

52:08.226 --> 52:10.593
It happens
when the sun goes down,

52:10.595 --> 52:13.195
right before it disappears.

52:13.197 --> 52:18.701
It's really rare,
but I've seen it happen once.

52:18.703 --> 52:20.703
It's supposed to mean
good luck.

52:32.917 --> 52:36.552
It only really happens
in pollution anyway.

52:49.367 --> 52:52.234
Oh, hey!

52:52.236 --> 52:54.303
I was wondering
what happened to you two.

52:54.305 --> 52:55.337
Did you find him?

52:55.339 --> 52:56.805
No.

52:56.807 --> 52:58.874
Well, the man likes to wander.

52:58.876 --> 53:02.678
Where is he, really?
What's going on with him?

53:04.282 --> 53:06.849
Well, he's here.

53:06.851 --> 53:08.651
Stay there.

53:22.867 --> 53:25.301
There, you see?
[chuckles]

53:32.443 --> 53:35.811
Oh, I'm getting so old.
I'm so sorry.

53:37.882 --> 53:39.915
This is him.

53:40.918 --> 53:42.918
This is all him.

53:44.989 --> 53:47.523
He's all here.

53:50.995 --> 53:52.962
That's mine.

53:52.964 --> 53:55.297
That should never
have been in there.

54:11.549 --> 54:14.350
Why didn't you show me
these things earlier?

54:14.352 --> 54:15.651
He just dropped it by.

54:15.653 --> 54:17.653
Didn't even bother
to wake me up.

54:17.655 --> 54:19.288
He must know you're in town.

54:19.290 --> 54:21.257
Where is he going?

54:21.259 --> 54:23.892
If you didn't find him
at Murphy's Ranch...

54:23.894 --> 54:26.695
Shady Acres.
He's gonna be at Shady Acres.

54:26.697 --> 54:27.997
A rehab?

54:27.999 --> 54:30.466
No, no, no, no, no!

54:30.468 --> 54:32.268
It's a refuge.

54:32.270 --> 54:34.603
To get off the drugs
you got him on?

54:34.605 --> 54:37.706
I didn't get your dad on drugs.

54:37.708 --> 54:39.475
I might do a little
smokey-smoke, kiddo,

54:39.477 --> 54:42.945
but your old man,
he likes to self-medicate,

54:42.947 --> 54:44.947
and there's nothin'
he won't take.

54:47.285 --> 54:49.985
You don't mind me asking,

54:49.987 --> 54:52.354
why do they call you Gangrene?

54:58.796 --> 55:03.666
This is what happens
when you cut your foot,

55:03.668 --> 55:09.004
and you don't get it
taken care of in time.

55:09.006 --> 55:10.339
What do you think?

55:10.341 --> 55:12.875
Is that making you happy?

55:12.877 --> 55:15.511
Your father carved that.

55:15.513 --> 55:18.747
He did such a good job,
nobody knows I even have it.

55:18.749 --> 55:20.916
I can walk a couple of feet,
you don't even tell.

55:20.918 --> 55:24.386
You don't have to cut
your toenails anymore.

55:24.388 --> 55:28.357
No, but the termites,
my dear, are a bitch.

55:35.933 --> 55:38.767
So do you know what you're gonna
say to him when you see him?

55:38.769 --> 55:40.502
Not at all.

55:42.606 --> 55:45.007
How 'bout we practice?

55:45.009 --> 55:47.676
I'll be Simon,
and you can be you.

55:47.678 --> 55:49.078
Okay.

55:51.782 --> 55:53.849
[Southern accent]
Hiya, Fern.

55:53.851 --> 55:56.685
Hey, Dad. Didn't know
you were a Southerner now.

55:56.687 --> 55:58.887
Do you remember me?

55:58.889 --> 56:02.024
I spent some time
in the Ozarks.

56:02.026 --> 56:03.592
Oh.

56:03.594 --> 56:06.095
I did a lotta thinkin'
back there.

56:06.097 --> 56:09.431
I... I thought about you.

56:12.937 --> 56:16.672
I understand if you
don't wanna forgive me.

56:16.674 --> 56:18.941
Yeah, I know, I get it.

56:18.943 --> 56:22.578
You're a pretty
messed-up dude.

56:22.580 --> 56:25.848
Guess I can't blame you
for being the way you are.

56:25.850 --> 56:27.649
Maybe I'm the same way.

56:27.651 --> 56:30.085
You think you're the sa--
I mean...

56:30.087 --> 56:33.622
You think
we're the same way?

56:33.624 --> 56:36.458
Guess we'll see.

56:36.460 --> 56:39.561
Mental illness
comes out in your 20s.

56:39.563 --> 56:41.997
Did for you, right, Pops?

56:50.474 --> 56:52.408
That's my girl.

56:56.147 --> 56:59.481
[phone chiming]

57:03.821 --> 57:05.120
Um, hello?

57:05.122 --> 57:06.855
<i> SEAN: Wyatt, my man.</i>

57:06.857 --> 57:09.558
Yeah, Mom, do you mind
if I just call you back later?

57:09.560 --> 57:12.728
Yeah, I'll talk to you soon,
okay? Love you too. Bye.

57:14.031 --> 57:16.031
Why is your mom calling
right now?

57:16.033 --> 57:20.002
Um, she's just, uh...
She's just emotional.

57:20.004 --> 57:22.538
She really wanted me
to move back.

57:22.540 --> 57:24.039
Are you going to?

57:24.041 --> 57:26.041
No.

57:26.043 --> 57:30.112
Why would I...
I mean, are you...

57:30.114 --> 57:32.748
Where are you
gonna go anyway,

57:32.750 --> 57:35.584
after we figure this all out?

57:35.586 --> 57:37.119
Hey, guys, come down.

57:37.121 --> 57:39.721
I got some drinks
with your names on 'em.

57:39.723 --> 57:41.690
Come on, let's go.

57:42.827 --> 57:45.027
- Shall we?
- Yep.

57:47.565 --> 57:49.798
[laughing]

57:49.800 --> 57:53.735
- It was Barrett's girlfriend?
- Yes!

57:53.737 --> 57:56.839
In India, we don't even talk
to a girl before we're married.

57:56.841 --> 57:59.475
It is ridiculous!

57:59.477 --> 58:02.144
Hey, we need shots.

58:02.146 --> 58:03.479
Really?

58:03.481 --> 58:04.680
No more shots.

58:04.682 --> 58:07.950
More shots, more shots,
more shots!

58:07.952 --> 58:10.018
- More shots?
- More!

58:10.020 --> 58:11.520
- More.
- No!

58:11.522 --> 58:13.021
Yes.

58:13.023 --> 58:15.657
Here, you get the big one,
big guy.

58:15.659 --> 58:16.859
- Great.
- He's my bestie best.

58:16.861 --> 58:18.193
Here you go.

58:18.195 --> 58:19.795
- Thanks, bestie.
- Here you go, man.

58:19.797 --> 58:22.898
And okay, we're gonna toast.

58:22.900 --> 58:25.167
To friendships.

58:28.272 --> 58:32.007
[coughing]

58:32.009 --> 58:33.108
No more.

58:33.110 --> 58:35.677
Yeah, hits the spot.

58:35.679 --> 58:38.247
- I can't--
- [phone chiming]

58:41.552 --> 58:46.121
Um, hey, guys,
I gotta go make a phone call.

58:46.123 --> 58:47.556
No!

58:47.558 --> 58:48.657
Yeah, no, don't worry.

58:48.659 --> 58:50.726
I'll be back. I'll just...

58:50.728 --> 58:52.261
FARID: Don't go.

58:52.263 --> 58:54.296
- This is our time, man!
- What a mama's boy.

58:54.298 --> 58:56.832
- Don't go on without me, okay?
- Okay.

58:56.834 --> 58:58.967
What a fuddy-duddy.

59:00.804 --> 59:03.539
I think I'm gonna go to sleep.

59:05.776 --> 59:09.211
MAHONEY: Hey, that's not--
that's not the couch.

59:09.213 --> 59:11.079
<i> SEAN: Keep suckin'</i>
<i> on these teats, Wyatt.</i>

59:11.081 --> 59:12.981
<i> You're makin' mama proud.</i>

59:12.983 --> 59:16.218
About that,
I was trying to cover.

59:16.220 --> 59:18.220
<i> Oh, you can call me Mom.</i>
<i> That's cool.</i>

59:18.222 --> 59:23.258
You know, your story's
really interesting, by the way.

59:23.260 --> 59:25.294
Thanks.

59:25.296 --> 59:27.162
My mom left
when I was little too.

59:27.164 --> 59:29.264
Wyatt told you about my--

59:29.266 --> 59:31.066
Was I not supposed to know?

59:32.970 --> 59:34.670
<i> We need it by next week.</i>

59:34.672 --> 59:37.339
No problem, I just...

59:37.341 --> 59:40.208
I don't know. I think
I should tell her, honestly.

59:40.210 --> 59:41.910
<i> Think about</i>
<i> what's important, okay?</i>

59:41.912 --> 59:43.679
<i> Your career or this girl?</i>

59:43.681 --> 59:45.614
I know, I know.

59:49.720 --> 59:52.321
Ooh, okay.

59:52.323 --> 59:55.891
You know, it's pretty insane
that you live in that car.

59:55.893 --> 59:58.093
Why do you say that?

59:58.095 --> 1:00:00.329
I mean, you're
way too attractive for that.

1:00:00.331 --> 1:00:02.664
Um...

1:00:02.666 --> 1:00:05.000
Thanks.

1:00:05.002 --> 1:00:07.703
I mean, you could totally pull
off living in your car though.

1:00:07.705 --> 1:00:10.372
[laughing]

1:00:10.374 --> 1:00:12.374
I concur.

1:00:12.376 --> 1:00:14.042
<i> Look, Wyatt, you're good,</i>

1:00:14.044 --> 1:00:16.211
<i> and we could really</i>
<i> use a guy like you.</i>

1:00:16.213 --> 1:00:17.946
- You mean that?
<i> - Of course, man.</i>

1:00:17.948 --> 1:00:19.381
<i> There's been talks</i>
<i> about moving you up</i>

1:00:19.383 --> 1:00:21.817
<i> to full-time</i>
<i> fuckin' staff writer.</i>

1:00:21.819 --> 1:00:27.122
That's-- That's amazing.
I would really like that.

1:00:27.124 --> 1:00:28.290
[laughs]

1:00:30.828 --> 1:00:34.930
So much body and volume.

1:00:34.932 --> 1:00:38.066
Look at that beautiful shine.

1:00:38.068 --> 1:00:41.336
Is that Pantene?

1:00:41.338 --> 1:00:44.806
- Yes, it is! Very good.
- [laughing]

1:00:46.977 --> 1:00:48.076
[sniffs]

1:00:49.113 --> 1:00:51.279
Is that Head & Shoulders?

1:00:51.281 --> 1:00:53.281
Yeah, it is!
[laughs]

1:00:53.283 --> 1:00:55.283
I knew it.

1:00:59.390 --> 1:01:00.956
No, of course.
[hiccup]

1:01:00.958 --> 1:01:03.859
I-- I really wanna work
with you guys.

1:01:03.861 --> 1:01:07.095
That's all I ever wanted.

1:01:07.097 --> 1:01:09.398
<i> Then finish the job.</i>

1:01:11.869 --> 1:01:14.302
Okay, no, um, I'm sorry.

1:01:14.304 --> 1:01:17.039
I'm just really drunk and--

1:01:17.041 --> 1:01:19.207
- Yeah, I am too.
- I have to go.

1:01:20.411 --> 1:01:23.412
[vomits, groans]

1:01:23.414 --> 1:01:25.113
Fuck.

1:01:41.799 --> 1:01:43.899
I just woke up.

1:01:43.901 --> 1:01:46.702
What happened last night?

1:01:46.704 --> 1:01:48.470
We got drunk.

1:01:48.472 --> 1:01:50.472
Well, I know you got drunk.

1:01:53.110 --> 1:01:55.177
You slept over.

1:01:55.179 --> 1:01:57.245
Yeah, I know.

1:01:57.247 --> 1:01:59.848
I don't even remember
falling asleep.

1:01:59.850 --> 1:02:01.983
I found you on the floor.

1:02:04.088 --> 1:02:06.088
Yeah, that sounds like me.

1:02:10.728 --> 1:02:12.728
I need to eat.

1:02:13.797 --> 1:02:16.064
You wanna go somewhere?

1:02:16.066 --> 1:02:18.166
No, I've got stuff to do.

1:02:21.472 --> 1:02:24.005
But I thought we were
going to the ranch.

1:02:28.078 --> 1:02:30.879
- Okay, what's up?
- Nothing.

1:02:30.881 --> 1:02:32.881
Are you angry at me?

1:02:32.883 --> 1:02:35.517
No, I--
I just gotta go.

1:02:35.519 --> 1:02:37.352
Fern, wait.

1:02:51.235 --> 1:02:54.970
Oh, man, dude,
my head's killing me.

1:02:59.476 --> 1:03:02.944
Hey, should we be
concerned about Farid?

1:03:02.946 --> 1:03:05.213
Fern was acting
really weird this morning.

1:03:05.215 --> 1:03:08.850
Kinda left without saying bye.

1:03:08.852 --> 1:03:11.253
Well, she does have ovaries.

1:03:12.856 --> 1:03:14.923
Oh, fuck me.

1:03:14.925 --> 1:03:16.792
MAHONEY: There's my champ.

1:03:20.164 --> 1:03:24.299
Did anything strange happen
last night after I left?

1:03:24.301 --> 1:03:26.902
No. We just talked.

1:03:26.904 --> 1:03:28.904
Just talked, huh?

1:03:32.543 --> 1:03:35.410
I was asleep, bro.

1:03:35.412 --> 1:03:37.412
Drunk as hell.

1:03:39.116 --> 1:03:41.116
What happened last night?

1:03:45.455 --> 1:03:48.156
We just made out for a second,
and she backed away.

1:03:48.158 --> 1:03:50.025
- I'm sorry.
- Oh, yeah, no, no, no.

1:03:50.027 --> 1:03:51.827
I got the story, man.
I get it. No, no.

1:03:51.829 --> 1:03:54.296
I had a few drinks in me,
I was getting a little wasted,

1:03:54.298 --> 1:03:56.131
one thing led to another,
before you know it,

1:03:56.133 --> 1:03:57.999
I got my hand around her,
yeah, I got it!

1:03:58.001 --> 1:03:59.568
I made a mistake.

1:03:59.570 --> 1:04:02.871
You know, I would expect
this stuff from Barrett,

1:04:02.873 --> 1:04:05.140
this being Scum Palace
and all, but you?

1:04:05.142 --> 1:04:06.541
I thought it would
help the story.

1:04:06.543 --> 1:04:08.343
How does that make any sense?

1:04:08.345 --> 1:04:12.147
You're way too invested in her.
You said it yourself.

1:04:12.149 --> 1:04:14.916
This should be about business,
not romance.

1:04:14.918 --> 1:04:16.051
Can't you see that?

1:04:16.053 --> 1:04:18.053
I want you to move out.

1:04:21.491 --> 1:04:22.591
You don't mean that.

1:04:22.593 --> 1:04:24.392
Why wouldn't I?

1:04:24.394 --> 1:04:26.161
We're geography friends.

1:04:26.163 --> 1:04:30.532
I only hang out with you
because I live with you.

1:04:30.534 --> 1:04:32.067
If I met you on the street,

1:04:32.069 --> 1:04:33.602
if I just didn't
even really know you,

1:04:33.604 --> 1:04:36.404
I would never
hang out with you.

1:04:36.406 --> 1:04:39.307
I thought it wasn't
about her, man.

1:04:39.309 --> 1:04:43.211
She doesn't even know about
the articles yet, does she?

1:04:47.217 --> 1:04:50.085
I'm sorry that
you had to witness that.

1:04:50.087 --> 1:04:52.254
I'm disappointed
in the both of you.

1:05:04.368 --> 1:05:06.067
I'm low on coolant.

1:05:06.069 --> 1:05:07.969
Yeah, me too.

1:05:14.211 --> 1:05:16.278
So you wanna talk
about Mahoney?

1:05:19.650 --> 1:05:23.151
I'm sorry.
I shouldn't have.

1:05:25.289 --> 1:05:26.421
Do you like him?

1:05:26.423 --> 1:05:27.622
No. He's repugnant.

1:05:27.624 --> 1:05:30.325
So why did you do it then?

1:05:30.327 --> 1:05:32.193
I'm low on oil too.

1:05:32.195 --> 1:05:34.195
Could you just stop looking at
your fucking car for a second

1:05:34.197 --> 1:05:35.263
and talk to me?

1:05:35.265 --> 1:05:36.564
You know what?

1:05:36.566 --> 1:05:39.367
Maybe I'm just not ready
for this, okay?

1:05:43.640 --> 1:05:45.307
Why are you shutting down?

1:05:45.309 --> 1:05:47.309
'Cause that's what I do.

1:05:49.947 --> 1:05:51.446
You said to me--

1:05:51.448 --> 1:05:53.348
You said you were scared
of happiness back in the woods

1:05:53.350 --> 1:05:56.217
because it ends eventually,
right?

1:05:56.219 --> 1:05:58.653
Everything ends when you die,
so what, does nothing matter?

1:06:00.324 --> 1:06:02.324
I can't believe it, Fern,

1:06:02.326 --> 1:06:05.093
like after everything that
we've been through together,

1:06:05.095 --> 1:06:07.562
after everything
I've done for you, you just--

1:06:07.564 --> 1:06:09.397
You just go behind my back.

1:06:09.399 --> 1:06:11.499
It was just overwhelming, okay?

1:06:11.501 --> 1:06:12.600
So I freaked out.

1:06:12.602 --> 1:06:15.337
I freaked out because...

1:06:15.339 --> 1:06:16.972
because I like you.

1:06:16.974 --> 1:06:17.405
I like you a lot.

1:06:22.179 --> 1:06:23.645
I just thought
it would be a way out,

1:06:23.647 --> 1:06:26.581
and I wouldn't
have to be scared.

1:06:28.352 --> 1:06:32.454
I've had a lot of broken
relationships in my life, Wyatt.

1:06:33.523 --> 1:06:34.990
I'm sorry.

1:06:34.992 --> 1:06:38.693
It didn't mean anything
to me, okay?

1:06:38.695 --> 1:06:42.063
Can we just forget about it?

1:06:42.065 --> 1:06:43.598
Please?

1:07:02.386 --> 1:07:05.787
Honestly, I don't care anymore.
Let's just--

1:07:05.789 --> 1:07:07.789
Let's just go to the ranch.

1:07:07.791 --> 1:07:09.791
Let's find your dad.

1:07:12.362 --> 1:07:14.362
We're so close.

1:07:17.034 --> 1:07:18.500
Thanks.

1:07:19.603 --> 1:07:21.603
You're a good person, Wyatt.

1:07:27.177 --> 1:07:29.277
No, I'm not.

1:07:30.514 --> 1:07:32.313
I'm not, actually.

1:07:32.315 --> 1:07:35.283
Fern, I should tell you.

1:07:35.285 --> 1:07:36.418
Um...

1:07:37.554 --> 1:07:39.120
What?

1:07:39.122 --> 1:07:41.289
I...

1:07:42.759 --> 1:07:44.359
What is it?

1:07:44.361 --> 1:07:46.094
What?

1:07:48.799 --> 1:07:51.199
Wyatt?

1:07:51.201 --> 1:07:52.567
Wyatt.

1:07:52.569 --> 1:07:54.302
[snoring]

1:07:55.705 --> 1:07:57.405
Just sleep.

1:07:57.407 --> 1:07:59.507
It's okay.

1:07:59.509 --> 1:08:01.276
Just sleep.

1:08:07.584 --> 1:08:12.687
So what were you gonna tell me
right before you passed out?

1:08:12.689 --> 1:08:14.689
Oh, I don't remember.

1:08:15.692 --> 1:08:17.358
The place is so green.

1:08:25.569 --> 1:08:27.335
It does exist.

1:08:27.337 --> 1:08:29.871
I guess this is it.

1:08:32.776 --> 1:08:35.777
Dr. Green wasn't
lying to us after all.

1:08:37.147 --> 1:08:39.447
Look, they have archery.
Exciting.

1:08:39.449 --> 1:08:41.282
Stop the car.

1:08:41.284 --> 1:08:42.484
- Stop the car!
- Okay, okay!

1:08:50.861 --> 1:08:56.197
<i> ¶¶ [guitar, whistling]</i>

1:08:58.301 --> 1:09:00.301
- I knew it.
- He can paint too.

1:09:04.674 --> 1:09:05.740
Simon?

1:09:09.613 --> 1:09:10.712
Simon!

1:09:10.714 --> 1:09:11.813
Hey, look, look.

1:09:11.815 --> 1:09:13.515
Look at that one over there.

1:09:58.328 --> 1:09:59.394
Hi.

1:09:59.396 --> 1:10:01.763
Hi. I'm Bill.

1:10:01.765 --> 1:10:04.866
I run Shady Acres.

1:10:04.868 --> 1:10:06.367
Hey, I'm Wyatt.

1:10:06.369 --> 1:10:08.636
Nice to meet you, Wyatt.

1:10:08.638 --> 1:10:10.638
And you must be Fern.

1:10:10.640 --> 1:10:11.973
Yeah.

1:10:11.975 --> 1:10:14.342
Your father told me
you'd come.

1:10:15.779 --> 1:10:18.980
Your likeness is
all over this place.

1:10:20.217 --> 1:10:22.250
So what do you guys do here?

1:10:22.252 --> 1:10:26.421
We provide help
to anyone who needs it.

1:10:26.423 --> 1:10:28.856
Let me show you.

1:10:30.493 --> 1:10:35.697
Here we rehabilitate
the mind, body, and soul.

1:10:35.699 --> 1:10:37.532
These are the main grounds.

1:10:37.534 --> 1:10:40.268
Some of the buildings
are a little drab,

1:10:40.270 --> 1:10:44.305
but your father was commissioned
to put a friendly face on them.

1:10:44.307 --> 1:10:46.441
- See that mural right there?
- Mm-hmm.

1:10:46.443 --> 1:10:48.876
Your father painted that.

1:10:48.878 --> 1:10:53.314
Simon was
an incredibly talented man.

1:10:53.316 --> 1:10:55.850
What do you mean, was?

1:11:02.859 --> 1:11:05.426
He used to talk about you

1:11:05.428 --> 1:11:07.929
like you were always
in communication.

1:11:07.931 --> 1:11:09.931
What's with
all the past tense?

1:11:16.473 --> 1:11:18.806
Fern...

1:11:18.808 --> 1:11:21.943
your dad passed
four months ago.

1:11:23.313 --> 1:11:27.382
It was peaceful,
in his sleep.

1:11:28.818 --> 1:11:30.418
I'm so sorry.

1:11:34.391 --> 1:11:36.391
I'll give you a moment.

1:11:41.731 --> 1:11:43.798
Fern...

1:11:43.800 --> 1:11:45.800
Fern, I'm sorry.

1:11:49.039 --> 1:11:51.539
I can't believe he left again.

1:11:52.909 --> 1:11:55.343
He didn't even wait for me.

1:12:05.955 --> 1:12:07.822
He's gone.

1:12:09.526 --> 1:12:11.793
Don't, don't say that.
I mean...

1:12:13.997 --> 1:12:15.430
WYATT: I'm sorry.

1:12:17.967 --> 1:12:19.901
I wanna go home.

1:12:19.903 --> 1:12:21.436
Okay.

1:12:38.755 --> 1:12:40.455
What was he like?

1:12:40.457 --> 1:12:42.724
He was a good friend.

1:12:42.726 --> 1:12:44.726
I didn't know much
about his past.

1:12:44.728 --> 1:12:46.094
[chuckles]

1:12:46.096 --> 1:12:49.097
Well, I don't even think
he knew.

1:12:49.099 --> 1:12:52.066
He just told me
that he had a daughter,

1:12:52.068 --> 1:12:54.769
and everything he did
was for her.

1:12:54.771 --> 1:12:57.772
I don't think
I'll ever understand him.

1:12:57.774 --> 1:13:01.909
Your dad suffered from
schizophrenia, big time.

1:13:01.911 --> 1:13:06.547
He was picked up for roaming
the streets, sometimes naked.

1:13:06.549 --> 1:13:08.916
On more than one occasion,
we petitioned the authorities

1:13:08.918 --> 1:13:14.389
to let him stay here,
rather than be sent to prison.

1:13:14.391 --> 1:13:16.824
Simon was no criminal.

1:13:16.826 --> 1:13:19.761
He just had
mental health issues.

1:13:19.763 --> 1:13:21.129
He looked happy.

1:13:21.131 --> 1:13:24.565
He was great,
when he was taking his meds.

1:13:24.567 --> 1:13:26.868
Easy to get along with.

1:13:28.438 --> 1:13:30.905
I'm glad you came, Fern.

1:13:32.742 --> 1:13:34.909
He's still here,
in a way.

1:13:37.647 --> 1:13:40.648
[birds chirping]

1:13:51.528 --> 1:13:53.060
Where's his grave?

1:13:53.062 --> 1:13:55.997
There isn't one.

1:13:55.999 --> 1:13:59.100
Someone picked up his ashes from
the mortuary before we could.

1:14:01.671 --> 1:14:03.438
